ZH: 我在钱包里找到了一张百元钞票。
EN: I found a hundred yuan bill in my wallet.

ZH: 他花了很多钱在新手机上。
EN: He spent a lot of money on a new phone.

ZH: 这张银行卡里还有多少钱？
EN: How much money is left in this bank card?

ZH: 我们必须存一点钱作为紧急备用。
EN: We need to save some money for emergencies.

ZH: 他把所有的钱都投资在了股市上。
EN: He invested all his money in the stock market.

ZH: 你可以通过手机轻松地转钱给朋友。
EN: You can easily transfer money to friends through your phone.

ZH: 这个商店接受所有类型的钱。
EN: This store accepts all kinds of money.

ZH: 这项服务需要额外支付一些钱。
EN: This service requires an extra payment.

ZH: 我们需要一些钱来支付旅行的费用。
EN: We need some money to cover the expenses of the trip.

ZH: 老板今天给我加了一点钱。
EN: The boss gave me a little extra money today.

ZH: 我们应该认真对待每一分钱的花费。
EN: We should be careful with every penny we spend.

ZH: 我们应该珍惜自己辛苦挣来的钱。
EN: We should cherish the money we work hard for.

ZH: 他在赌博上输光了所有钱。
EN: He lost all his money gambling.

ZH: 他经常借钱，却很少还。
EN: He often borrows money but seldom repays.

ZH: 我们决定慷慨解囊为慈善事业捐款。
EN: We decided to generously donate money to charity.

ZH: 他的家族有很多钱，但是他不依赖家庭财富。
EN: His family has a lot of money, but he doesn't rely on family wealth.

ZH: 他把钱都用来买彩票了。
EN: He used all the money to buy lottery tickets.

ZH: 赚钱容易，守住钱难。
EN: Making money is easy, keeping money is hard.

ZH: 钱不是万能的，但没有钱是万万不能。
EN: Money isn't everything, but without money, nothing is possible.
